        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 18 at 2:13PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 213 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southeast of Etoile, or 23 miles east of Lufkin, moving
southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Broaddus.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
